org.corfudb.annotations

Annotation Type Mutator


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Inherited
public @interface Mutator
    Marks a mutator, which is a method on an object to be recorded in the Corfu log. Mutators modify the state of an object but do not access it. Created by mwei on 1/7/16.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String conflictParameterFunction
      The name of the function used to generate conflict parameters, which will be used to generate conflict information.
      String name
      The name of the mutator, which will be written to the log.
      boolean noUpcall
      Whether or not we should generate an upcall for this mutator.
      boolean reset
      Whether this mutator resets the state of this object.
      String undoFunction
      The name of the function to undo this mutation, which needs to belong to the same object.
      String undoRecordFunction
      The name of the function which will be called prior to applying this mutator, which will be used to generate an undo record.

      • conflictParameterFunction

        public abstract String conflictParameterFunction
        The name of the function used to generate conflict parameters, which will be used to generate conflict information.
        Returns:
        The name of a conflict generation function.

      • reset

        public abstract boolean reset
        Whether this mutator resets the state of this object. Typically used for methods like clear().
        Returns:
        True, if the mutator resets the object.
        Default:
        false

      • noUpcall

        public abstract boolean noUpcall
        Whether or not we should generate an upcall for this mutator. If set to true, no upcall will be generated - this is typically used when providing a mutator-only version of a mutatorAccessor (for example, "blindPut" and "put").
        Returns:
        True, if no upcall should be generated.
        Default:
        false
